    "# HashGuard-Med — Secure Image Database for Trustworthy Chest X-ray Classification\n",
    "\n",
    "**End-to-end experiment notebook (Kaggle).** Run cells top to bottom.\n",
    "\n",
    "Pipeline: build secure DB module → select balanced subset → ingest with hash-chain + signatures →\n",
    "train baseline ResNet (unsecured vs secured loader) → run 3 attacks → measure poison impact →\n",
    "collect tables & figures → save everything to `/kaggle/working`.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Before running:**\n",
    "1. Right panel → **Add Input** → attach a NIH ChestX-ray14 dataset that contains the PNGs\n",
    "   (e.g. *NIH Chest X-ray 14 (224x224 resized)*). If your image dataset does **not** include\n",
    "   `Data_Entry_2017.csv`, also attach the original *NIH Chest X-rays* dataset (it is only mounted,\n",
    "   not downloaded, so it costs no time) for the labels.\n",
    "2. Right panel → **Accelerator** → **GPU** (P100 or T4).\n",
    "3. Right panel → **Session options** → Internet can stay **off** (nothing is downloaded).\n"
